Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.27,0:00:06.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is... Earth?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.39,0:00:32.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hovering!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.01,0:00:44.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The situation's level of \Ndanger has climbed by 255%.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.57,0:00:46.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I propose a preemptive attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.76,0:00:48.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.62,0:00:51.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell them in words they can understand \Nthat we mean them no harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.73,0:00:54.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.89,0:00:56.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It talked!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.59,0:00:58.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We deny hostility.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.67,0:01:00.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there another one of 'em inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.74,0:01:02.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We wish you to lower your weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.97,0:01:09.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Ridget, the Fleet Commander's Aide.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.69,0:01:11.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.33,0:01:15.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's asking for your name and affiliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.67,0:01:16.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.67,0:01:24.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Ensign Ledo, pilot of the anti-Hideauze \Nannihilation weapon, Chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.49,0:01:26.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.81,0:01:28.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Annihilation weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.94,0:01:30.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is Hideauze?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.31,0:01:32.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy. Coexistence is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.81,0:01:34.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You are all fellow humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.88,0:01:36.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Join Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.01,0:01:38.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We request dialog.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.49,0:01:39.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is your commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.28,0:01:41.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber! What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.29,0:01:47.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In their language, I requested a dialog \Nand told them the Alliance's purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.25,0:01:50.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. But why are they \Nacting hostile toward us?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.39,0:01:52.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Throw down your weapon! And \Nwhoever's inside there, get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.94,0:01:54.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's she saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.31,0:01:55.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cannot comprehend.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.18,0:01:57.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This machine is unmanned.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.94,0:02:00.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.02,0:03:35.02,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,The Planet of Origin
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.21,0:03:46.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy, you're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.97,0:03:49.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The delivery was late, \Nso I had to make up time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.81,0:03:50.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.40,0:03:54.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know your impression of that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.10,0:03:56.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You talked to him too, Ridget. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.94,0:03:59.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who's come \Nin closest contact with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.15,0:04:01.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So what's he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:03.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.54,0:04:04.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Normal?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.80,0:04:10.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it was like his first time here, so he \Nwas surprised and all, "What should I do?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.21,0:04:14.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And it didn't seem like \Nhe intended to hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.73,0:04:16.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although he did kind of touch my butt...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.83,0:04:17.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your butt?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.83,0:04:21.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I did sort of understand what the person \Ninside the Yunboro was trying to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.67,0:04:23.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you try asking him directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.28,0:04:24.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.69,0:04:26.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do if he goes wild?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.78,0:04:29.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the guy who wrecked \Nthe hangar with one stroke!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.23,0:04:30.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.67,0:04:33.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You examined that Yunboroid, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.57,0:04:36.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I got no idea what it's made \Nof or how it's put together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.86,0:04:39.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't even fit a knife into a seam.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.47,0:04:40.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing's one tough son of a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.23,0:04:42.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you, Bellows?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.47,0:04:44.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there anything unusual \Nwhen you brought it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.26,0:04:47.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno... I just did what \Nthis guy asked me to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.98,0:04:50.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,pull something up\N that looked valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.66,0:04:51.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.66,0:04:53.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The crane's trashed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.18,0:04:55.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think that Yunboro \Nwas gonna be so heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.88,0:04:57.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send you my bill later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.79,0:04:59.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your skills just weren't up to snuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.61,0:05:00.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.72,0:05:03.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander Fairlock...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.82,0:05:05.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.04,0:05:08.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that Yunboroid is the \Nproduct of high level technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.21,0:05:11.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to take it apart \Nand study it, if possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.58,0:05:13.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.82,0:05:16.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That mech's different from any \Ntreasure we've ever dredged up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.31,0:05:18.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's bust the thing open already!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.24,0:05:22.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Drag out the kid and the guy \Ninside and deep six 'em both!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.40,0:05:23.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not going to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.51,0:05:26.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What if they have comrades? Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.12,0:05:29.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It could lead to the whole \Nfleet being endangered.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.96,0:05:31.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand your line of thought, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.98,0:05:33.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, what a drag!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.38,0:05:35.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Fleet Commander is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.49,0:05:37.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd be sitting ducks if \Nmore came to settle a score.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.32,0:05:44.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I fail to see the logic in your actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.38,0:05:47.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please explain the reasoning \Nbehind prolonging this stalemate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.30,0:05:51.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This machine has more than enough armaments \Nto deal with the current situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.99,0:05:53.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For the moment, this is the best option.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.98,0:05:55.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Reasonable Course of Action:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.20,0:05:59.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,1. Overpower the armed ones \Nand bring them under control.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.12,0:06:02.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,2. Neutralize the nerve center \Nand suppress any retaliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.49,0:06:05.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber. Our immediate priorities \Nin these circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.21,0:06:08.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,are establishing contact with our \Ntroops and determining our location.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.17,0:06:15.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't figure it out, then maybe we \Ncan rely on any archives these people have.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.27,0:06:17.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed, with reservations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.81,0:06:21.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's important is that Earth, \Nas a planet, supports life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.42,0:06:27.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're told that abnormal solar activity \Nmade Earth a frozen, dead planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.54,0:06:29.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.37,0:06:30.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.79,0:06:34.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Securing a habitable planet is \Nthe Alliance's most fervent wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.51,0:06:40.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With this world's abundant water and air, \Nit could replace Avalon as our new hub.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.97,0:06:44.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Suggestion: I believe that judgment goes \Nbeyond the limitations of your post.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.57,0:06:46.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're probably right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.47,0:06:49.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How about communicating with the Alliance?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.13,0:06:52.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I continue to send out a distress \Nsignal, but have received no reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.89,0:06:56.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you continue to operate on your own \Nlike this, you won't be able to obtain
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.18,0:07:00.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,necessary military supplies, which will \Nthen bring on trouble with your metabolism.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.91,0:07:02.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Reasonable Course of Action 3:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.58,0:07:04.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you should consider \Nescaping these surroundings
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.19,0:07:07.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and going back into suspended animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.79,0:07:15.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.85,0:07:17.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Pinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.18,0:07:19.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's gonna fix my boat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.24,0:07:20.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me, dumbass!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.97,0:07:25.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.98,0:07:27.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.54,0:07:34.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.46,0:07:37.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the merman like?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.32,0:07:38.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Merman?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.76,0:07:40.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A boy took you hostage, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.86,0:07:42.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How old is he? Is he handsome?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.78,0:07:46.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,People keep bugging me to ask you about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.31,0:07:48.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme a break! I'm trying to work here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.02,0:07:52.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:54.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't jump until the wings are spread!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.27,0:07:56.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You need to be more careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.79,0:08:14.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm supposed to keep my mouth shut after \NRidget and them snatched my treasure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.55,0:08:17.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll thoroughly search the exact same spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.49,0:08:30.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bebel, I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.22,0:08:31.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.07,0:08:34.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I took so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.62,0:08:37.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.97,0:08:39.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you were taken hostage?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.85,0:08:42.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.30,0:08:44.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm lucky he wasn't a dangerous person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.48,0:08:46.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, his name is Ledo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.43,0:08:48.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo... What's he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.46,0:08:51.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd guess he's about my age.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.30,0:08:54.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With his slim arms, he doesn't \Nseem really masculine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.43,0:08:55.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.68,0:08:59.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's one more, still inside a Yunboro.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.11,0:09:02.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That one can speak a little bit of our \Nlanguage, enough to understand him anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.73,0:09:06.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then they should talk things over \Nwith them and become friends, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.31,0:09:10.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly! That's what I think too, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.82,0:09:14.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. I brought you a present.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.43,0:09:21.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.76,0:09:22.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you can use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.57,0:09:23.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.42,0:09:31.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A perfect fit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.28,0:09:33.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.93,0:09:36.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.81,0:09:40.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could talk to Ledo, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.47,0:09:44.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he may have \Ncome from the heavens...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.92,0:09:47.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From the heavens? Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.27,0:09:49.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! You know the legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.93,0:09:54.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,About the people who escaped to the \Nstars when the Earth froze that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.02,0:09:56.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's just a fairy tale!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.77,0:09:59.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, that Yunboro was \Nbrought up from the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.78,0:10:04.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-uh. I bet they came from space.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.65,0:10:08.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The people that escaped into space \Nlong, long ago have come home!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.95,0:10:13.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Space, huh? I don't know if they'd \Nbother coming all this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.16,0:10:18.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Oldham said that if a ship \Nkept going all the way up,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.53,0:10:20.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,it would take just half a \Nday for it to reach space!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.38,0:10:33.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.72,0:10:53.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.48,0:10:58.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Fleet Commander said we mustn't \Nprovoke him, which is understandable...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.11,0:10:59.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...but we can't just do nothing, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.71,0:11:01.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And so you chose {\i1}her{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.47,0:11:04.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we had any other volunteers... \NDo you want to take her place?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.59,0:11:05.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.54,0:11:09.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conjecture: The threat level is minimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.12,0:11:13.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that she's been \Nsent as an envoy to negotiate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.72,0:11:15.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Envoy? She's a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.79,0:11:17.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I intercept her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.29,0:11:18.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.85,0:11:19.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.07,0:11:44.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the corpse of an aquatic animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.25,0:11:45.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Corpse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.12,0:12:07.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What does she want me to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.20,0:12:08.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conjecture: It is harmless food.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.93,0:12:10.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me she wants me to eat it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.37,0:12:12.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conjecture: It is a friendship ritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.61,0:12:15.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a corpse!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.05,0:12:16.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I leave the choice to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.02,0:12:24.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber, ask her what her objective is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.22,0:12:30.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She seeks conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.22,0:12:32.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.23,0:12:40.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He ate it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.18,0:12:49.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She says her name is Amy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.99,0:12:52.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She asks where you came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.13,0:13:00.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The heavens?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.63,0:13:11.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So you two are soldiers fighting \Nagainst those Hideauze?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.24,0:13:12.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.21,0:13:14.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then are you stronger than them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.56,0:13:16.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Super... strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.75,0:13:21.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From space, seriously? \NThen Bebel was right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.36,0:13:28.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth is different than \Nit appears in our records.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.26,0:13:29.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I seek explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.70,0:13:32.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're getting better and better \Nat speaking our language.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.73,0:13:37.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Interpreting must be tough. Won't \Nyou at least show me your face?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.61,0:13:39.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, show my face?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.58,0:13:42.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you're inside of there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.69,0:13:45.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no one inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.29,0:13:52.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It really is empty...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.98,0:13:56.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a Pilot Support Enlightenment \NInterface System.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.81,0:14:00.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,System? Then that machine is talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.96,0:14:06.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber is an artificial intelligence that \Naids in battle and maintaining life support.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.92,0:14:08.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.86,0:14:10.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.01,0:14:11.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! Wow! Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.85,0:14:14.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There really is no one in \Nhere! You're a machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.78,0:14:18.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I repeat the question. About the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.75,0:14:20.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! Wow! Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.40,0:14:28.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're told that it was a giant lump of ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.42,0:14:31.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it melted and became a water planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.70,0:14:37.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, there were supposedly these places \Ncalled "land", but I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.65,0:14:42.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, everyone lives on ships that \Nare grouped together like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.79,0:14:47.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ancient ships and materials are all sunk at \Nthe bottom, so we hoist them out of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.89,0:14:51.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gargantia, too... That's \Nthe name of this fleet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.24,0:14:52.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.99,0:14:54.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gargantia?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.38,0:14:56.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh. Gargantia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.08,0:14:57.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,More exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.55,0:15:01.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there are other fleets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.37,0:15:03.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Small ones, big ones...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.14,0:15:06.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When ships join up, it doesn't \Ntake long to form a fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.49,0:15:10.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And there are pains in the \Nneck, too, like pirates...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.30,0:15:13.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pirates are enemies?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.89,0:15:15.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess you could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.54,0:15:19.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.27,0:15:27.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A Milky Way. Sometimes \Nit's called a Sea Galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.12,0:15:29.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to see it. It's so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.57,0:15:34.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.34,0:15:37.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can travel on a new Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.93,0:15:39.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is a Milky Way?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.22,0:15:42.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a glowing path that \Nruns through the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.62,0:15:45.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We wouldn't be able to live without it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.75,0:15:49.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So the ships forge ahead, \Nstaying on the path.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.54,0:15:52.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no guarantee that \Nthe path will go on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.21,0:15:54.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So when that happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.90,0:15:57.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,we search for a new Sea Galaxy \Nand switch over to that path.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.15,0:16:02.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lightbugs are what make Sea Galaxies glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.34,0:16:06.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're a swarm of itty-bitty \Nbugs that accumulate electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.73,0:16:10.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We get our electricity \Nfrom this band of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.31,0:16:24.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.20,0:16:29.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.11,0:16:32.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? What's your analysis \Nof our coordinates?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.30,0:16:35.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to the existence of an \Natmosphere, lack of information,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.22,0:16:37.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and the limitations of optical analysis,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.54,0:16:41.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,further observation is required \Nto derive our current position.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.19,0:16:53.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true, I tell you! I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.03,0:16:56.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You think they'd come up with \Na better lie than that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.34,0:16:59.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If that really is a talking machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.68,0:17:00.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It {\i1}is!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.90,0:17:04.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that's true, come on, \Na war with an alien race?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.37,0:17:06.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.44,0:17:11.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But that aside, let's find out for sure \Nif it can talk or not by taking it apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.17,0:17:12.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we throw the kid overboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.59,0:17:13.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.87,0:17:16.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in trouble and has nowhere else to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.12,0:17:18.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, listen to what Ledo has to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:23.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Having undue contact with an outsider \Nwouldn't benefit either side...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.55,0:17:26.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not the sea... and not space...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.52,0:17:34.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirming the terrain...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.10,0:17:37.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no mistake. This is \Nwhere the Yunboro was sunken.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.16,0:17:39.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's get psyched up and do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.89,0:17:53.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They've got an abundance of commodities here
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.45,0:17:55.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and the threat level of these natives is low.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.46,0:17:57.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed, with reservations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.86,0:18:00.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can't return to the \Nfront under our own power,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.00,0:18:04.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,all we can do is wait for the troops \Nto notice our distress signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.58,0:18:07.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the best course of action is \Nto look for a cooperative relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.47,0:18:08.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.67,0:18:16.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The front. Troops. The people who live on \Nthis planet don't know what those words mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.65,0:18:20.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The desperate struggle against the \NHideauze... has no connection to this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.75,0:18:28.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.40,0:18:31.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, what's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.24,0:18:33.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The salvage ship is under \Nattack from pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.55,0:18:34.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bellows's ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.65,0:18:37.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bellows and the others are...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.56,0:18:46.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.60,0:18:49.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're surrounding us! \NEscort Fleet Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.85,0:18:52.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No good! There are too many of 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.85,0:18:57.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Salvage team, stand by underwater!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.50,0:18:59.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are several new points of engine noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.82,0:19:00.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Check it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.81,0:19:01.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.55,0:19:06.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.34,0:19:24.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kites?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.65,0:19:35.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy has nine ships \Nand several small crafts!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.36,0:19:37.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're starting a kite attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.49,0:19:38.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the reinforcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.59,0:19:39.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if they'll make it in time...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.99,0:19:41.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.55,0:19:43.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You two are strong, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.72,0:19:45.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a totally strong Yunboro, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.65,0:19:47.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do something! Help us out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.79,0:19:49.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She seeks assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.77,0:19:52.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it. This'll be \Na good bargaining chip.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.85,0:19:58.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Activate floater!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.21,0:20:09.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.08,0:20:11.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That Yunboro's starting to move!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.06,0:20:12.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.95,0:20:22.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do they intend to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.53,0:20:24.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Liftoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.51,0:20:42.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Bellows from Gargantia?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.26,0:20:45.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You got what you came for! \NNow get the hell out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.80,0:20:50.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dump that rinky-dink fleet \Nyou're with and join us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.18,0:20:52.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Empress Lukkage recognizes your skills, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.97,0:20:56.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make me laugh, pirate scum!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.71,0:21:00.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.05,0:21:02.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For your own good, I'd think \Ntwice about refusing...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.54,0:21:03.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.12,0:21:11.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Identification of main \Nenemy targets complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.50,0:21:13.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Request to identify smaller targets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.99,0:21:14.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.34,0:21:27.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Identification complete. \NDeflector beam stand by.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.64,0:21:30.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Annihilate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.82,0:21:41.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.42,0:21:42.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.86,0:21:45.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.63,0:22:03.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,G-Good lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.05,0:22:09.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world...?
